# Bug Report

**Bug ID:** BUG-001

**Title:** Clicking the filter dropdown arrow does not open the dropdown menu

**Severity:** Low

**Priority:** Medium

**Environment:**
- Application: Sauce Demo
- URL: https://www.saucedemo.com
- Browser: Google Chrome Version 149.0.7827.156 (64-bit)
- Operating System: Windows 11 Pro

---

## Preconditions

1. User is logged in as a Standard User.
2. User is on the Products page.

---

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Navigate to the Products page.
2. Locate the Product Sort dropdown in the upper-right corner.
3. Move the mouse cursor over the dropdown arrow.
4. Verify the cursor changes from an arrow to a hand.
5. Click directly on the dropdown arrow.

---

## Expected Result

The dropdown menu opens when the user clicks the dropdown arrow.

---

## Actual Result

Clicking directly on the dropdown arrow does not open the dropdown menu. The dropdown only opens when another area within the dropdown control is clicked.

---

## Frequency

100% (Occurred every time during testing.)

---

## Status

Open

---

## Notes

The cursor changes to a hand when hovering over the dropdown arrow, indicating that the arrow is clickable. However, clicking the arrow has no effect, creating inconsistent and potentially confusing user interaction.
